/-!
# Reflection infrastructure

This umbrella re-exports the M4 reflection stack:

* `Comparison`: the raw Kummer-pairing component comparison.
* `Local.Basic`: the global prime `lambda = (ζ_p - 1)`, the localized
  cyclotomic ring at `lambda`, its maximal ideal, and the principal-unit
  filtration `U_n = 1 + lambda^n O_F`.
* `Local.Filtration`: the formal subgroup API for the principal-unit filtration.
* `Local.RootsOfUnity`: the localized cyclotomic root-of-unity subgroup inside
  `U_1`.
* `Local.PowerMap`: the positive-step filtration estimate for the local
  `p`-power map.
* `Local.Endpoint`: the formal endpoint subgroup `mu_p * U_2` and its
  immediate `p`-power consequences.
* `Local.Graded`: the first graded map `U_1 -> m / m^2` and its kernel.
* `Local.Completion`: the completed local principal-unit filtration used for
  the reverse endpoint p-power map.
* `Local.UnitQuotient`: the completed local principal-unit mod-`p` quotient
  and its additive `ZMod p` structure.
* `Local.DeltaAction`: the cyclotomic `Delta` action on lambda-local units
  and stability of the local principal-unit filtration.
* `Local.ComponentDimension`: the local mod-`p` quotient character-projection
  target for the REF-11d dimension assembly.
* `Kummer.Singular`: REF-15b — instantiation of `Kummer.Basic`'s abstract
  Kummer-extension API on the singular `η` produced by REF-13/14, with
  `(η : K) ∉ K^{×p}` derived from singular nontriviality, hence the Kummer
  extension `K(η^{1/p})` is a nontrivial degree-`p` extension. Includes the
  Dedekind-domain helper that the fractional-ideal group is torsion-free.
* `Kummer.TameCriterion`: REF-18 ↔ Reflection bridge — atomic per-prime
  refinement of the umbrella Kummer-Dedekind unramified obligation
  `KummerDedekindUnramifiedAt P v` into the **tame** atom
  `TameKummerCriterion P v` (intended discharge route: discriminant of
  `X^p − γ` at `v ∤ p`), plus the two trivial discharges
  `count v γ = 0` and `(p : ℤ) ∣ count v γ`. Documents the substantive
  Mathlib content (ramification index `e(P|v) = gcd(count v γ, p)` mod
  units) that would discharge the criterion non-trivially.
* `Kummer.WildCriterion`: REF-18 ↔ Reflection bridge — companion atomic
  refinement of the **wild** case `v ∣ p` of `KummerDedekindUnramifiedAt`,
  splitting into `KummerWildLocalLift` (Hensel lift `γ ≡ β^p mod v^{p+1}`),
  `KummerWildValuationStep` (local `p`-th power ⟹ `v_v(γ) ∈ p · ℤ`), and
  the composite `KummerWildCriterion P v`. Provides `IsAboveP v` /
  `IsCoprimeToP v` as the tame/wild dichotomy variable, the trivial
  discharge from a global `p`-th power, and the global assembly
  `kummerDedekindUnramified_of_wild_and_tame` that combines the wild and
  tame atoms back into the umbrella per-prime obligation.
* `ResidueSymbol.Furtwaengler.OneSidedKummerReciprocity`: the direct
  one-sided principal reciprocity theorem target used for the
  principal-ideal vanishing step.
* `ComponentReflection.Basic`: the readable component-index reflection target.
* `SingularKummer.FiniteGroupComparison`: the finite-group comparison between
  `A / pA` and `A[p]`.
* `SingularKummer.SingularPair`: singular pairs `(I, alpha)` with `(alpha) = I^p`
  and their map to `A[p]`.
* `SingularKummer.Equivariance`: equivariance of the singular exact sequence under
  automorphisms preserving principal fractional ideals.
* `SingularKummer.ComponentChoice`: the elementary component-lifting lemma used after
  component surjectivity.
* `SingularKummer.ComponentProjection`: component surjectivity for ranges of commuting
  projection operators.
* `SingularKummer.CyclotomicAction`: the actual cyclotomic `Delta`-actions on `S`
  and `A[p]` used to instantiate the REF-08 dimension bound.
* `SingularKummer.DimensionLowerBound`: the REF-08 lower bound
  `dim S_i >= 2` from the singular exact sequence, a unit line, and nonzero
  target component.
* `SingularKummer.ElementaryQuotientComponent`: the elementary quotient `V = A / pA`
  and its induced character components.
* `SingularKummer.CharacterProjection`: additive `ZMod p` character projections for
  `Delta = (ZMod p)ˣ`.
* `SingularKummer.CharacterProjectionEigen`: the eigenspace relation satisfied by the
  character-projection range.
* `SingularKummer.CharacterProjectionIdempotent`: identity-on-range and idempotence
  facts for character projections.
* `SingularKummer.FiniteLevelAdditiveProjection`: exact finite-level projections for
  additive actions.
* `SingularKummer.FiniteLevelCoefficientReduction`: coefficient reduction for exact
  finite-level idempotents.
* `SingularKummer.FiniteLevelFinalBridge`: assembly of the finite-level quotient and
  torsion comparisons.
* `SingularKummer.FiniteLevelIdempotent`: exact character idempotents over finite
  coefficient rings `ZMod m`.
* `SingularKummer.FiniteLevelProjectionBridge`: the finite subgroup bridge from
  `V_i` to the corresponding projected `A[p]` component.
* `SingularKummer.FiniteLevelQuotientComparison`: comparison of the exact finite-level
  projection subgroup with the elementary quotient component `V_i`.
* `SingularKummer.FiniteLevelTorsionReduction`: reduction of finite-level character
  relations on `p`-torsion to the mod-`p` projected component.
* `SingularKummer.GlobalUnitKernel`: the short exact sequence
  `0 → E/E^p → S → A[p] → 0` with `E = (𝓞 K)ˣ`.
* `SingularKummer.SingularZMod`: additive `ZMod p` module structures on `S` and `A[p]`.
* `SingularKummer.SingularLinearAction`: conversion of multiplicative actions to
  additive `ZMod p`-linear actions.
* `SingularKummer.SingularClassChoice`: the final lift from a nontrivial target
  character projection to a singular class.
* `SingularKummer.ProjectedFiniteComparison`: finite comparison on projected components.
* `SingularKummer.ProjectedSubgroupComparison`: finite comparison through a projected
  subgroup of `A`.
* `SingularKummer.IntegralCharacterProjection`: integer-coefficient lifts of the
  mod-`p` character projections.
* `SingularKummer.SingularRepresentative`: extraction of concrete singular-pair
  representatives.
* `SingularKummer.Localization`: REF-12 localization from singular classes to
  the local-unit quotient at a height-one prime.
* `SingularKummer.LocalizationKernel`: REF-13 dimension-kernel choice for
  localization, including a singular-pair representative form.
* `SingularKummer.TorsionComponent`: the projected component notation for `A[p]`.
* `RankInequality`: insertion of the unit-quotient odd-vanishing input.
* `Boundary`: the `j = 1` boundary component handled through Herbrand.
* `Final`: the class-number divisibility transfer used by `Main`.
* `FinalRegularPrime`: regular-prime degenerate dispatcher for the
  class-number transfer (`dvd_h_of_dvd_hPlus_of_subsingleton_class_group`
  and an `IsRegularPrime`-flavoured corollary), discharging the chain
  vacuously.
* `ClassNumberCriterion`: the abandoned reflection-route class-number
  criterion, retained without restating Kummer's criterion.
* `KummerToUnitQuotientComposer`: end-to-end composer feeding
  `KummerCharacterUnitLift.OfComponentExtensions`, with the per-extension
  pipeline, the per-character `HomPromotion` recipe, and trivial-case
  discharges.
-/
